title: school athletes of the week
text:
The Dispatch high-school Athletes of the Week, based on performances from Oct. 12-18:
Cameron Karmia BEXLEY, BOYS GOLF Karmia, a senior, shot a 1-under-par 143 for co-medalist honors with Connor Quigley of Dayton Oakland in leading the Lions to the Division II championship at NorthStar Golf Club in Sunbury.
Olivia Kompa and Paige Kompa UPPER ARLINGTON, GIRLS TENNIS Olivia, a senior, right, and Paige, a freshman, won the Division I doubles championship. The sisters avenged their only postseason loss by beating Anna Delaney and Alexis Steer of Olentangy Liberty 6-2, 6-0 in the final after downing Golden Bear teammates Kyra Jung and Anna Reynolds 6-3, 6-1 in a semifinal.
Karmia and the Kompas will receive plaques from Motorists Insurance. Coaches are encouraged to email sports@dispatch.com or fax 614-461-8798 by 4 p.m. Mondays with nominations. 


In addition to the two Athletes of the Week,  The Dispatch  recognizes a top performer in each sport in season:
Alex Cash WORTHINGTON KILBOURNE, BOYS SOCCER Cash, a senior defender, scored three first-half goals to help Kilbourne build a 4-1 lead, then helped the Wolves shut out Olentangy Orange in the second half to win the Ohio Capital Conference Capital Division title.
Sam Buck REYNOLDSBURG, GIRLS SOCCER Buck, a junior forward, scored four goals in the teamâ€™s last regular-season match, a 5-0 win over Groveport, to help the Raiders win their first OCC Ohio Division game of the season.
Shannon Maloney WATTERSON, FIELD HOCKEY Maloney, a senior, scored twice in both a 3-1 win over Hudson and a 4-0 victory over Bexley and added a goal in a 2-1 victory over Upper Arlington.
Lucas Bons DUBLIN COFFMAN, BOYS CROSS COUNTRY Bons, a sophomore, took first place out of 68 runners in 15 minutes, 20.23 seconds to win the OCC Central Division race. Coffman edged Thomas Worthington 39-43 for the championship.
Allison Guagenti OLENTANGY ORANGE, GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY Guagenti, a freshman, topped a field of 67 runners to win the OCC Capital Division championship race in 18:42.67. She won by
42 seconds. Her victory powered Orange to the team title with 27 points.
Liz Kim DUBLIN COFFMAN, GIRLS GOLF Kim, a junior, shot 2-over-par 74 at the Links in Groveport for medalist honors in leading the Shamrocks to their fourth straight Division I district championship. She had three birdies and won by five strokes.
Natalie Regula JONATHAN ALDER, VOLLEYBALL Regula, a senior setter, had three aces, six kills, 97 assists, 230 setting attempts and eight digs in 3-0 victories over Highland, River Valley and Fairbanks. She had only three service errors and two hitting errors.
Jordan Leasure AMANDA-CLEARCREEK, FOOTBALL Leasure, a senior running back and linebacker, led 1-6 Amanda to a 29-28 upset of 6-1 Logan Elm. He rushed for 263 yards on 29 carries, scored three touchdowns and the deciding two-point conversion, blocked a field-goal attempt and made a game-sealing interception. He also made nine tackles, two for losses.
